<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST1894>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Emmrald Glanderlin<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Wednesday, March 20, 2002 - 05:21 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> She recognized the handwriting immediately.  It was strong, yet poetic.  Eloquent, but familiar words invited the entire clan to gather at the Chief’s request.  The parchment was tacked up in a few strategic places.  Everyone who was anyone in Axepeak would be there.  Especially with the mention of feasting and ale.  <BR> <BR>&#34;Be inturestin’ ta sees ‘ow me Sis gonna prepares such a spread,&#34; Emmrald chuckled.  &#34;Mebbe I best see if’n she needs a bit o’ ‘elp.&#34; <BR> <BR>Her own delves were tidy if empty these days.  The coals burned merrily in the hearth.  Jewel framed portraits on the mantle served as reminders of the family who once lived here.  &#34;Aye, tis time I got out among me kin more of’n,&#34; mused Emmy as she collected her cooking and cleaning utensils into a large traveling pack.  &#34;I ken Di ‘as nae bu’ impulments o’ torstin’ in ‘er delves.  Better go make sure’n dat dis party be nae like tha wun she an’ me throw’d all dem years ago fer Storm an’ Stark!&#34; <BR> <BR>When she arrived at her newlywed sister’s new delves it was to hear the dulcet tones of Dimond’s voice, &#34;Nae comes back witout enough food ta feeds tha clan, an hurry they&#39;ll be here in a few hours!&#34; <BR> <BR>Emmrald sidestepped MoradinSon, as he went off on his appointed mission.  &#34;Sonn Ultok, Emmykins!&#34; he smiled.   <BR> <BR>&#34;Sonn Ultok ta ye, me brudd’r,&#34; she chuckled.   &#34;Findar torst wi’ yer shoppin!&#34;  <BR> <BR>Dimond was beginning to replace various weapons and pieces of armor to their racks when Emmrald let herself in.  &#34;Duz ye need enny ‘elp wi’ things, Sis?&#34; she asked.  Spying a helm half full of stale Cheefydoodles on the couch, Emmy nodded.  &#34;I brung me arsenal,&#34;  she announced taking a mop and a broom from her pack.  &#34;Furst we attacks tha livin’ room.  Den we plans tha menyoo, eh?&#34; <!-/Text-!> <P> 
