efore any more baskets escaped.  The tiny basket wafted out of the box and settled on the ground, rapidly expanding in size till it was large enough to require two dwarfs to easily carry!  The breadfruits smelled delicious and although his dwarven kin stepped away from the clearly magical basket with ominous looks of suspicion in thier eyes, the badger was more interested in pilfering a treat for himself. <BR> <BR>&#34;Well, wha&#39;s wrong wi&#39; ye lads?  Fetch up thi&#39; basket afore the badger eats all the goodies..I has a banquet tae deliver!&#34; <BR> <BR>&#34;Jarghed giant had best deliver those kegs an nae just drink um&#34; grumbled Storm as he and his kin headed for home. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
