<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST2017>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Solla Elfhunter<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Tuesday, April 23, 2002 - 10:34 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> It&#39;s a beautiful day for hunting, Solla thought, as she whistled and walked down the path.  Her quiver was full, her spear was sharp and she could smell fresh game in the air.  Ah, it was good to be alive!  It was a grand day to go hunting, but no need to hunt alone, when she was walking right past Diamond&#39;s house. <BR> <BR>Solla poked her head into the kitchen window and said, &#34;Hey, Di, want to go hunting?&#34; Too late she saw Diamond huddled over a potatoe, ruining a perfectly good knife blade.  She backed quickly away and turned to run, but she wasn&#39;t quicker than Emmrald.  Faster than a dwarf can say, I&#39;ll take another keg, she was seated next to Diamond with a potatoe in her hand. <BR> <BR>&#34;Gest what we needed, extrie help,&#34; said Emmrald smiling happily. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
