<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST2018>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Diamond<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Wednesday, April 24, 2002 - 09:59 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> The dwarven hunter looked over at Solla with a woeful look, &#34;Ye cin this be all Storm&#39;s fault.  He goes an invites folk over wit nae a word ta me, then wanders off ta &#39;find food&#39;.  What&#39;s duz I end up doin?  Peelin tators!&#34;  She holds up the vile root and pontificates. &#34;Alla me life when there be a dinner ta be made, I get sat at a table with this evil vegetable and tolt ta peels that skin off.&#34;  She stands, warming to her tirade, holding her potato in the air, &#34;Who says tha skin must be peelt off?!  Is tha skin so worthless ta be scraped frum the body o its tator only ta be thrown mercilessly ta trash heap?!  Nae, I says!  Tator skins has valuey!  I says, leave them ta adds a new flavor ta our meals!&#34;   <BR> <BR>Di finishes her sermon o tha sprout and reaches to drain her tankard, then notices Emmy and Solla staring at her.  &#34;What?&#34; she asks as she sits back down to the table, &#34;Just tryin ta live&#39;n things up in tha kitchen, is all.&#34; <!-/Text-!> <P> 
