<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST2020>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:emmrald@bestweb.net"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Emmrald Glanderlin Hammersmith<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Wednesday, April 24, 2002 - 04:25 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> The delves were starting to fill with rich smells as some of the traditional dwarven cooking neared completion.  A knock at the door brought a lass looking for Dimond.  Emmrald right away enlisted the lass, poured her an ale and handed her a paring knife.  &#34;Sonn Ultok! Goo&#39; ta meets ye, Solla!  We cin use more &#39;elp fer dis feast! Arau Thalorn ta ye fer stoppin&#39; by!&#34; <BR> <BR>While Emmy went to check the roasts and breads she heard muttering and came back to hear a finer sermon than she&#39;d heard in the temple either of Brell or Eir and to rival some of the ones from clerics of Berronar and Moradin himself.  The fact that it centered on a potato was touching, too. <BR> <BR>&#34;Ye ken whut, Sis? ye be rite! We gonna bake tha rest!&#34; Emmrald announced to the two warriors trapped in the kitchen.  &#34;But we needs sum o&#39; dat shiney foily stuff.&#34;  Emmy looked around. <BR> <BR>&#34;Ye gots enny ol&#39; armor or shields whu&#39; Storm wi&#39; nae miss, Di?  If&#39;n we &#39;ammer on &#39;em an&#39; make &#39;em thin enuf ta wrap tha taters, they taste mighty fine.  O&#39; carse dey be better if&#39;n we rubs &#39;em wi&#39; oil an garlic furst.&#34; <BR> <BR>While the two kuldresses looked at one another wondering if Emmrald had gone mad, she grabbed a pair of aprons for them.  &#34;Ye cin nae werks in a kitchen in yer battle gear, Lasses!  Puts dese on!&#34;   <BR> <BR>&#34;When we gits ta &#39;taters in tha fire, ye cin &#39;elps me turn tha roasts!&#34; <!-/Text-!> <P> 
