<!-Post: 2047-!><!-Time: 1020521656-!>
<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST2047>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="javascript:alert('The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.')" onMouseOver="window.status = 'The e-mail address and profile information for the individual posting this message is not available.'; return true"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Diamond<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Saturday, May 4, 2002 - 10:14 am:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> Diamond gave her sister a sober look as Solla ran off towards the forge, obviously released from the kitchen prison and running for her life.  &#34;Sis, ye ken all tha old armor be in THA Room.&#34;  There was an ominous silence as a fearful look passed between the two siblings.  A nod of understanding passed between them and Diamond pulled a rusty key from a hook on the kitchen pantry wall as she walked out the back door in the direction of a dark little used tunnel. <BR> <BR>Some would have thought it strange that she took her spear with her or that she had grabbed up the last handful of stale beef jerky in the pantry.  The huntress stoically traveled down several other dark and web covered tunnels to the back of the cheef&#39;s delves and stopped in front of a heavily fortifide and bolted door. <BR> <BR>Bracing herself against the door, she unbolted and unlocked it, then readied her spear.  Scurrying and shuffling could be heard in the confines of the piles of stored goods as she opened the door.  Stepping into the room, she quickly reclose the door as if to not allow something to escape, and peered about for some armor she could use. <BR> <BR>The huntress&#39;es trained ears could hear the stealthy shuffle in the back of the room slowly creeping in her direction.  &#39;Gah! Tha thing be stalkin folk now,&#39; she thought with a scowl.   <BR> <BR>Spotting a couple a discarded breastplates in Storm&#39;s scrap pile, Diamond knew she had to move quickly before the beast could get upon her.  Taking the handful of jerky from her pocket, the dwarven lass threw it will all of her might to the back of the cavern room.  The hardened jerky crashed into an old shield that toppled over resulting in loud crashes and clatters. <BR> <BR>There was a protective growl of rage not five feet from Diamond in the midst of a pile of pole arms, then a line of toppling weapons and various armors as the creature ran off in the direction of the thrown jerky. <BR> <BR>Acting fast before the creature realized what she was doing, Diamond grabbed up two rusty old broken pieces, tucked them under each arm and made it out the door.  Not five seconds after the door was shut and bolted tight there was a heavy crashed against the inside of the door then a roar of anger. <BR> <BR>Long ago resigned to its fate, the creature only scratched and clawed at the iron clad door a few moments before it shuffled off to eat its jerky offering.  With a breath of relief, Diamond relocked the door, situated the armor pieces better for carrying and started back towards her delves muttering under her breath.  &#34;What&#39;d ye do wit tha pet wolverine tha&#39; I&#39;d nae let ye keep in tha house.&#34;  Taking on a deeper gruffy voice she muttered back to herself, &#34;Ye&#39;d be proud o me lass, I founds a way ta protects tha store room.&#34; <BR> <BR>She took the broken pieces to Solla at the forge, drew two tankards of ale from the forge keg and sat down on a stool nearby to chat and watch as the lass worked. <!-/Text-!> <P> 
