<TABLE BGCOLOR=#ccffff WIDTH=60% BORDER=0 BORDERCOLOR=#0000ff> <TR><TD><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" SIZE="3" COLOR="#000000"><FONT SIZE=-1> <A NAME=POST2061>  By <B><!-Email-!><A HREF="mailto:emmrald@bestweb.net"><!-/Email-!><!-Name-!>Emmrald Glanderlin Hammersmith<!-/Name-!></A></B> on Thursday, May 9, 2002 - 06:40 pm:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><P> <!-Text-!> &#34;I guesses sum nae likes bein’ near tha hearth,&#34; Emmy shrugged as the two lasses hightailed it out of the kitchen toward the forge.  She hung up the worn homespun aprons on hooks.   &#34;Ye’d think I offer’d dem sum kinda drowie nighties or sumthin!&#34; chuckled the younger Glanderlin Sister.   With a resigned sigh, Emmrald continued to prepare more food, turning a roast now, stirring some stew in between.    The bread had risen and she put it into the oven after sprinkling it with some savory seed.   <BR> <BR>&#34;Berronar, thankyee fer callin’ me ta yer ‘earth.  I dinna ken ‘ow me kin be more den skin an’ bones wi’ tha way dey cares fer wun anudder.&#34;   Stirring the coals of the fire she reconsidered.  &#34;Mebbe tha ale an’ torstin’ be enuf fer ‘em.  So long as dey all be Samman.&#34; <!-/Text-!> <P> 
